main event: A civilian observed a reddish round object with a flashing light hovering near San Angelo, Texas on 23 September 1966.
interesting points: The object was visible for approximately 28 minutes,The witness described the object as very bright and clear,The observer noted that the object was not a star as it moved and faded out twice before returning,The location of the observation was about two miles away and two miles in elevation from the observer,The weather conditions were reported as cloudless and calm.
sighted object: one reddish round object with a flashing light
witness description: Civilian, a 35-year-old housewife who had seen a similar object six months prior but did not report it
